## 5. Adding a new mechanism (checklist)

Use this for arm, shooter, flywheel, turret, or mechanisms not yet in Mantik lessons.

### Phase A — Research (do not code yet)

- [ ] Read mantik-pid-practice subsystem (if exists) or FRC lesson MDX
- [ ] Record: motor type, mass/inertia, gearing, sensor units, travel limits
- [ ] Record: which FF gains matter (kG/kV/kA), which PID gains, typical tuning order
- [ ] Record: lesson example values (hints only — do not hard-code as answers)
- [ ] Confirm control mode: position vs velocity vs motion profile

### Phase B — Physics module

- [ ] `dcMotor.ts` — already shared; pick correct `getNEO` / `getKrakenX60` / etc.
- [ ] `{mechanism}Plant.ts` — WPILib matrices + gravity/model specific term
- [ ] `{mechanism}Feedforward.ts` — correct WPILib FF class shape for that mechanism
- [ ] `{mechanism}Sim.ts` — PID + FF + plant step; ring buffer; subscribe API
- [ ] `{mechanism}Reference.ts` — plant defaults + `OPTIMAL_KP` + hint ranges
- [ ] `{mechanism}Sim.test.ts` — hold, drift, creep, kP low/optimal/high

### Phase C — UI (reuse patterns)

- [ ] Template + parser for subsystem constants
- [ ] Mechanism canvas (2D is fine for MVP)
- [ ] Wire into `PidSimApp` or mechanism picker on landing
- [ ] Code Tour + Tuning Guide step arrays (mechanism-specific)
- [ ] Cross-link from FRC lesson if applicable

### Phase D — Verify

- [ ] `npm run test:physics`
- [ ] `npm run build`
- [ ] Manual: kG (or kV) workflow matches lesson; kP optimal vs too high visible on TraceView; no lag on slider drag

